wiki.content:
"Catch My Breath" is a song by American recording artist Kelly Clarkson, from her first greatest hits album, Greatest Hits: Chapter One. One of the three newly-recorded songs for Chapter One, it was released as the album's lead single through RCA Records October 15, 2012. It was written by Clarkson, and co-written and produced by her musical director Jason Halbert, along with producer Eric Olson.
 
 Upon its release, "Catch My Breath" was met with positive reviews from music critics, who praised the song's uplifting theme and Clarkson's vocal performance. It has so far peaked on the Billboard Hot 100 at number 19 and has topped the Billboard Hot Dance Club Songs chart. It has also charted within the top ten of Adult Pop Songs, and on the top twenty of Pop Songs and Adult Contemporary charts.
